    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThis is how I use terminals inside Neovim:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1587\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1270688/231188066-d4dec544-ff3a-4026-8fad-fb5dfca2d285.png\">\r\n\r\nThere are 10 terminal instances associated to `<d-1>`, `<d-2>`, ... `<d-0>`.\r\n\r\nThe day floating windows were added to Neovim I implemented this with the help of a background window rendering the border and the header (at the time floating windows didn't support borders).\r\n\r\nOver time borders have been added to floating windows and recently we have titles, so I was thinking maybe I can get rid of the background window but I noticed the title can't be multiline. So I'm suggesting adding multiline titles for similar use-cases.\r\n\r\nWe can change the title type from string to string/string array, we can add an optional title_offset with the default value of 0 or floor(title_lines / 2) too.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe expected behavior is basically the image I attached above.",
